agreeToRefund(uint256).details: Called by either the buyer or seller to complete the 2 of 3 signatures needed to collect the refund.  This will calculate payouts, transfer funds and close out the exchange. Reverts if:   - caller is not the buyer or seller   - not in the 'Resolve' state   - resolve timer expired emits Refunded

complete(uint256).details: Complete an exchange.  Called by the Buyer. This finalizes the exchange and releases any escrowed funds. Reverts if:   - The caller is not the recorded buyer   - The exchange is not in the 'Fund' state emit Complete

createOffer((uint256,address,address,uin.details: Create a new Exchange. Called by the seller. Reverts if:   - buyer or seller addresses are 0x0   - the disputeTimer value is 0   - the caller is not the owner of the service referenced in _args Emits Offered

dispute(uint256).details: Called by buyer to dispute an exchange. Changes state to the dispute phase and starts the resolution timer. Reverts if:   - caller is not the recorded buyer   - not in the state of funded   - dispute time frame has expired   - price == 0.  As fee stuff does not have a dispute phase emits Disputed

fundOffer(uint256,(uint8,bytes32,bytes32.details: Commit to an offer.  Called by the buyer recorded in the exchange offer. On success it will transition to the 'Fund' state. If the offer has expired, it will be 'Voided' - no sale. Unless this is a free sale (price == 0), The buyer authorizes the exchange to transfer funds to escrow. Reverts if:   - the caller is not the recorded buyer   - the exchange is not in the 'offer' state.   - the buyer does not have enough money to escrow 'price' Emits 'Voided' if the offer expired, otherwise 'Funded'

params._permit: signed message from buyer to authorize the escrow

getEscrowBalance(uint256).details: Get the escrow balance for a given Exchange.  THis

returns.info: a memory version of the Exchange

isClosed(uint256).details: Check if the exchange is closed (complete or voided)

resolve(uint256,uint8).details: Called by the moderator to resolve a dispute.  Require 2 of 3 signatures to release funds. This call (from the moderator) counts as 1 of the required signatures. Changes the state to 'Resolve' Reverts if:   - caller is not the moderator   - not in the state of 'Dispute'   - the resolve timer has expired emits Resolved

params._rType: is the refund chosen by the moderator

triggerTimer(uint256).details: Update timers in the event of no activity. Called by the buyer or seller This is fail-safe to keep the exchange moving forward. A client can use 'callStatic' in ethers.js to simulate this call and determine whether trigger will fire anything (return true or false).  For example, if 'callStatic' returns true, you know a timer is expired and can then make the call without wasting a transaction. Reverts if:   - Caller is not the buyer or seller of the exchange emits Voided or Completed

returns._0: bool true if updated, false otherwise

documentation.text:
@dev Commit to an offer.  Called by the buyer recorded in the
 exchange offer. On success it will transition to the 'Fund' state. If the
 offer has expired, it will be 'Voided' - no sale.
 Unless this is a free sale (price == 0), The buyer authorizes the exchange
 to transfer funds to escrow.
 Reverts if:
   - the caller is not the recorded buyer
   - the exchange is not in the 'offer' state.
   - the buyer does not have enough money to escrow 'price'
 Emits 'Voided' if the offer expired, otherwise 'Funded'
 @param _exchangeId the exchange id
 @param _permit signed message from buyer to authorize the escrow

typeDescriptions.typeString: function () pure returns (struct BionetStorage storage pointer)

documentation.text:
@dev Complete an exchange.  Called by the Buyer. This finalizes the exchange
 and releases any escrowed funds.
 Reverts if:
   - The caller is not the recorded buyer
   - The exchange is not in the 'Fund' state
 emit Complete
 @param _exchangeId the exchange id

documentation.text:
@dev Called by buyer to dispute an exchange. Changes state to
 the dispute phase and starts the resolution timer.
 Reverts if:
   - caller is not the recorded buyer
   - not in the state of funded
   - dispute time frame has expired
   - price == 0.  As fee stuff does not have a dispute phase
 emits Disputed
 @param _exchangeId the exchange id

 needed to collect the refund.  This will calculate payouts, transfer funds

 Reverts if:

   - not in the 'Resolve' state
   - resolve timer expired
 emits Refunded

@dev Update timers in the event of no activity. Called by the buyer or seller

 A client can use 'callStatic' in ethers.js to simulate this call and
 determine whether trigger will fire anything (return true or false).  For
 example, if 'callStatic' returns true, you know a timer is expired and can
 then make the call without wasting a transaction.
 Reverts if:
   - Caller is not the buyer or seller of the exchange
 emits Voided or Completed
 @param _exchangeId the exchange id
 @return bool true if updated, false otherwise

@dev This facet defines the fair exchange protocol for services.
 It works through a series of state transistions to manage escrowed
 funds on behalf of a buyer and seller.
 A complete description of how it works, can be found here:
 https://github.com/synbionet/doc.synbionet/blob/main/docs/exchange.md
